<h2>LG Dryer Maintenance and Parts Replacement</h2>
<p>Regular maintenance extends your dryer's life significantly, but most homeowners skip it until something breaks. Our technicians recommend annual cleaning of the exhaust ductwork, especially in West Hollywood's older buildings where vents run longer distances to reach exterior walls. Lint builds up in places you can't see, reducing airflow and forcing your dryer to work harder. We also replace worn belts before they snap completely — a $40 part replacement versus a $120 emergency call when the belt breaks and leaves you with wet clothes. Door seals deteriorate over time, letting heat escape and reducing efficiency. Moisture sensors collect fabric softener residue that throws off their readings, causing over-drying or under-drying cycles. These aren't difficult fixes, but they require knowing what to look for and having the right tools. We offer maintenance visits that catch problems early, usually saving customers money in the long run compared to waiting for complete breakdowns.</p>
